Vice President Mike Pence delivered a commencement speech at the United States Coast Guard Academy's 137th graduation ceremony. He conveyed congratulations and greetings from President Donald Trump. Pence praised the graduates for their dedication and commitment to serving the nation. He also highlighted the historic investment in the military and the Coast Guard by the Trump administration. Pence emphasized the importance of the Coast Guard's role in protecting the nation from threats such as terrorism and drug trafficking. He commended the Coast Guard's response to the recent hurricanes and urged the graduates to lead with humility, self-control, and a servant's heart. Pence concluded by expressing his confidence in the graduates' ability to lead and serve the country.